<TEXT>
over tangiabrishin afghanistan ap tangiabrishin means 
ridge of silk and straddles the ancient trade route but helicopter 
crews flying convoy cover call it the wall of death 
nearly every day senior capt humayun his copilot and 
engineer have flown shotgun for trucks carrying food and weapons 
from kabul to jalalabad the eastern provincial capital under siege 
by moslem insurgents since march 7 
this is our job we do it for our homeland said the 
24yearold pilot who has been a member for six years of the 377th 
hero regiment based at the airport in kabul capital of afghanistan 
on wednesday he flew 13 western journalists the 75 miles to 
jalalabad in an mi8 chopper over the ridge bristling with 
guerrilla rockets escorted by five hind helicopter gunships it 
was the first trip to the city by western reporters since the siege 
began 
humayun says guerrillas shoot down one in four helicopters 
flying over the wall of death 
humayun lifted off from kabul airport crossed the mountains 
that surround the capital then settled his machine to an altitude 
of about 30 feet skimming at 160 mph over barren hills and valleys 
dotted with bombed mudandbrick houses and the burned wreckage of 
military vehicles 
the sarobi oasis where sporadic fighting has been reported 
flashed past below and the chopper climbed for tangiabrishin 
which loomed ahead within minutes 
over a deep gorge the crew began dropping decoy flares designed 
to deflect any heatseeking missiles insurgents might fire 
a wedge of three hind gunships led the passenger helicopter 
launching their own rockets occasionally breaking formation to fly 
laterally into gullies and pelt the ground with cannon and rocket 
fire 
with two gunships trailing humayun raced the mi8 through the 
canyons at 130 mph diving and weaving around hills and 
outcroppings using the terrain as natural cover 
ill fire the rockets if i suspet something is out there but 
that wont necessarily mean were under attack he said 
then he fired three rockets backfires jolted the helicopter and 
humayuns nervous passengers dived to the floor 
in 10 minutes the six aircraft were past the ridge of silk 
having bested the wall of death at least for now and humayun 
said the danger is over 
he guided the helicopter across the rocky plains and landed in a 
rice paddy on the outskirts of jalalabad a centuriesold way 
station between east and west near the khyber pass 
four hours later he returned to take the visiting journalists 
back to kabul this time with six attack choppers flying escort 
tangiabrishin was less than 20 miles away and this time the 
guerrilas fired two rockets 
humayun put the mi8 down in a shallow stream and two escorts 
hovered above while the other four circled nearby hills with guns 
blazing 
the young pilot jumped out of the helicopter when he returned 
moments later his passengers demanded to know why 
i was thirsty he said humayun grinned and returned to the 
cockpit 
with the way cleared he headed his aircraft for the ridge 
again he dropped flares fired rockets and dodged through the 
canyons then the seven choppers cleared tangiabrishin and 
clattered past sarobi 
humayun opened the cockpit door and pointed at the buildings in 
the distance 
kabul he said with a thumbsup 
the rebels control much of the countryside but they have yet to 
capture a major city capturing a city would give them a base for 
the interim government formed in pakistan in february and offer an 
alternative to the sovietbacked government in kabul 
president najib has said the 11yearold war will continue until 
all sides agree to sit down at the negotiating table he has called 
for direct talks with the united states which supports the 
guerrillas but washington has rejected the idea 
on thursday foreign minister abdul wakil said the failure of 
the jalalabad offensive proved a negotiated peace settlement was 
the only solution 
he said us policy would fail if the united states continues to 
support the rebels 
if america wants to give them more time to demonstrate their 
military power then all they will be doing is giving them more 
rockets he said theyve had time to show their power they 
have no power they only fire rockets 
</TEXT>
