here is a look at actions announced by 
president bush in response to the turmoil in panama 
the president thursday 
ordered an additional 2000 us troops into panama on top of 
the 10000 already there to protect the lives of american 
citizens more than 20000 us civilians many of them retirees 
live in the central american country 
denounced the regime of panamanian military leader gen manuel 
antonio noriega and said he is recalling us ambassador arthur 
davis bush said the embassy staff also will be reduced 
directed that us government employees and their dependents 
living outside of military bases be returned to the united states 
