<DOCNO> AP890512-0055 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
the army battalions on their way to panama 
include one from a light division organized for quick movement 
around the world and one from a standard mechanized division that 
trains to fight with personnel carriers and tanks 
the one company from the 2nd marine division meantime is the 
first to deploy on a realworld mission in what the corps calls its 
light armored vehicle or lav 
president bush ordered the battalions to panama on thursday 
the lav is an armored eightwheel personnel carrier that sports 
a 25mm chain gun which is a highspeed heavy type of machine gun 
as well as a 762mm machine gun 
the 7th light infantry division and the 5th infantry division 
are part of different corps within the army i and iii 
respectively and are based at different parts of the country 
fort ord calif and fort polk la 
they also reflect deliberately different capabilities 
the 7th known as the bayonet division was the first of four 
activeduty light infantry divisions created by the army during the 
reagan administration although the 7th has a long history as a 
regular army division it didnt become a light infantry division 
until oct 1 1985 
with about 10700 soldiers assigned to it instead of the roughly 
17000 assigned to a normal mechanized division the 7th is full of 
riflemen carries no heavy vehicles and deploys with only modest 
amounts of artillery and antitank weapons 
the idea behind the light divisions championed by former army 
chief of staff gen john wickham was to provide a president the 
option of using a fairly large force that could be moved rapidly 
around the world 
for example a normal heavy division such as those assigned to 
europe would require about 2850 flights of a c141 to deploy a 
complete light division could show up for combat with just 500 
flights 
the 7th was one of two army units the other being the 82nd 
airborne tapped for a similar emergency deployment to central 
america in march 1988 in that case the troops were sent to 
honduras because of incursions by nicaraguan troops 
the 5th infantry division meantime is a standard mechanized 
division whose history dates to world war i known as the red 
diamond division the 5th fought in four major campaigns during 
world war i and five major campaigns in europe during world war ii 
the 5th includes three activeduty mechanized brigades which 
rely on armored personnel carriers such as the m113 or the bradley 
fighting vehicle and three activeduty armor brigades equipped 
with m1a1 tanks 
one ranking military official said thursday a mechanized force 
was being sent as a precaution in case the situation in panama 
deteriorated further and additional protection was needed to help 
dependents evacuate 
although a mechanized infantry division can be transported by 
air the heavy equipment makes it a slow process in this case the 
pentagon announced the one battalion from the 5th would travel to 
panama by sea aboard the ship bellatrix 
the marines meantime are sending alpha co of the 2nd light 
armored infantry battalion that unit will be traveling by aircraft 
with 18 of the new lavs 
the 2nd marine division traces its roots to feb 1 1941 when 
it was formed for world war ii during that war the division 
fought in some of the bloodiest battles of the pacific including 
guadalcanal tarawa and okinawa 
the 2nd also went to lebanon in 1958 and 1982 to the dominican 
republic in 1965 and to grenada in 1983 it fights under the 
motto second to none 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

