a government body voted friday to pull 
out of a controversial danube river dam project it said is a 
symbol of hungarys mismanaged economic development the official 
news agency reported 
the decision came in the form of a proposal by an advisory body 
of the council of ministers but it serves as a strong indication 
the government and communist party leadership will scrap the 
project 
this will delight environmentalists who have said the nagymaros 
dam scheme will destroy wetlands and their unique wildlife and 
probably will anger czecholovakia which already has spent 11 
billion on a companion project 
the council of economists lawyers and other experts rejected 
the idea of putting the project to a public vote as suggested in a 
petition signed by 140000 hungarians the mti news agency said 
the body has stated categorically that no referendum should be 
held on the matter it reported in these complex questions of 
engineering economy and international law responsibility must not 
be passed on to hungarys citizens 
the multimilliondollar project to build dams and power stations 
at nagymaros 30 miles upstream from budapest and at gabcikovo in 
czechoslovakia was drawn up a decade ago with the intent of 
boosting electrical power for both communist nations and making the 
danube more navigable 
hungarian premier miklos nemeth told reporters earlier this week 
that the project stood a 5050 chance of being scrapped because it 
has become a symbol of a longoutdated economic model 
czechoslovakias investment in gabcikovo 40 miles east of 
bratislava may never be properly realized as experts say the 
projects are too interrelated for the gabcikovo dam to be fully 
effective without construction of the nagymaros segment 
mti said the advisory council believes that certain 
controversial issues are bound to occur even between friendly or 
allied states 
but the state agency said it expected no damage to relations 
between budapest and prague unless someone were to abuse the 
termination of the project for this purpose 
it quoted the government council as saying the project was 
misguided and badly handled all around 
terminating the project would not bring about an adequate 
situation either but this was the only alternative for the 
country mti concluded 
the agency said there was only one dissenting vote in the 
council but it did not say how many people serve on it 
