<TEXT>
rising business inventories combined with poor 
sales for the second consecutive month in march a sign of economic 
weakness the government said friday but economists said the trend 
is not worrisome yet 
the commerce department said inventories held on shelves and in 
back lots climbed 03 percent to a seasonally adjusted 7656 
billion in march following a 04 percent rise in february 
business sales meanwhile were unchanged at a seasonally 
adjusted 5073 billion after plunging 09 percent in february the 
sharpest fall since january 1987 
rising inventories unaccompanied by sales increases sometimes 
indicate a recession because manufacturers cut back production 
until inventories are sold off however analysts said stockpiles 
are not yet at troublesome levels 
inventories are fairly moderate said economist bruce 
steinberg of merrill lynch there does not seem to be an excess 
other than in the auto industry 
he said computerization and new inventory control techniques are 
enabling businesses to respond more quickly to changes and sales 
preventing large backlogs from building 
but economist robert g dederick of northern trust co in 
chicago said inventories do bear watching anything more than a 
moderate buildup could create a snapthewhip effect and topple 
the economy into a recession rather than the mild slowdown most 
economists expect 
we cant say theres been any rapid buildup but stocks 
have been rising rapidly enough that theyre vulnerable if sales 
growth remains sluggish he said 
march business activity left the ratio of inventories to sales 
at 151 meaning it would take 151 months to exhaust existing 
inventories at the march sales pace the ratio stood at 150 in 
february and 148 in january 
marchs rise in inventories was led by a 05 percent gain at 
manufacturing plants followed by a 04 percent climb in retail 
inventories and a 01 percent dip at the wholesale level 
in sales wholesalers showed a 02 percent gain and 
manufacturers posted a 01 percent decline sales were unchanged at 
retail stores in march an advance report on retail sales in april 
released thursday showed a modest 04 percent gain 
