the united states on friday told a unsponsored 
meeting of experts dealing with climate changes that washington now 
backed negotiations on a treaty to check the greenhouse effect a 
un official reported 
the official speaking on condition of anonymity said the 
united states announced it wanted to play a leading part in shaping 
a coordinated strategy to combat global warming caused by solar 
heat trapped under gases in the atmosphere 
he said washington now strongly backs un initiatives designed 
to lead to an international convention previously according to 
the official the united states had been not among the major 
supporters 
the meeting in geneva concluded friday it was held under the 
auspices of the un environment program and the world 
meteorological organization as part of an 18 monthstudy of 
climatic changes the experts will publish their recommendations 
next year 
scientists fear global temperatures could rise by four to nine 
degrees by the year 2050 such a warming trend could melt polar ice 
caps and cause sea levels to rise cause devere droughts and storms 
and disrupt the earths biological systems 
scientists will consider the results of fridays working group 
at a meeting of the intergovernmental panel on climate change in 
nairobi kenya next month 
