summer cochran said thursday 
the nations hay supply dropped by 10 million tons in 1989 and 
severe droughtinduced shortages in some midwestern states have 
caused iowa hay prices to skyrocket agriculture officials said 
the nations farmers had 1763 million tons of hay on hand as of 
may 1 1989 down from 2735 million tons at the same time in 1988 
according to figures released by the us agriculture department 
we had larger hay supplies on hand last year but they were 
quickly exhausted during the drought cochran said continued 
dry weather may cause this years smaller stocks to be depleted 
much further 
