opponents of the 6 billion seabrook nuclear 
reactor are seeking an emergency court order barring lowpower 
atomic tests at the embattled new hampshire plant 
a request for an immediate stay to block a lowpower license 
pending further judicial review was filed at the us circuit court 
of appeals here thursday by massachusetts the town of hampton 
nh the seacoast antipollution league and the new england 
coalition on nuclear pollution 
