bond gained 2 points last sept 2 the yield on the 30year 
government security dipped to its lowest level since early february 
yields on threemonth treasury bills plunged to 847 percent 
their lowest level since jan 3 
the surge in prices followed the labor departments report that 
wholesale prices rose 04 percent in april about half as much as 
some analysts had expected 
that tended to allay the markets fear that inflation was 
accelerating said william v sullivan director of money market 
research for dean witter reynolds inc it also suggested for the 
first time in well over a year that the fed may be in a position to 
ease credit policy 
the indication of an economic slowdown buttressed a government 
report thursday that showed retail sales up 04 percent last month 
well under the 13 percent many economists had expected 
sullivan said an economic slowdown along with lower prices could 
lead the federal reserve to relax its monetary policy encouraging 
lower interest rates and boosting the value of bonds 
people are thinking we are past the bulge in inflation caused 
by oil prices rising said robert brusca chief economist with 
nikko securities international inc 
the bond market had declined steadily this week until a small 
rise thursday amid pessimism over a lessthansatisfactory 
government quarterly refinancing auction and the belief that the 
wholesale prices would rise more 
in the secondary market for treasury bonds prices of shortterm 
governments were up by between point and 1 point intermediate 
maturities advanced by 1532 point and 1 points and longterm 
issues were up as much as 2716 points according to telerate inc 
the financial information service 
the movement of a point is equivalent to a change of 10 in the 
price of a bond with a 1000 face value 
the shearson lehman hutton daily treasury bond index which 
measures price movements on all outstanding treasury issues with 
maturities of a year or longer climbed 1383 to 114549 
the rise in the index was the largest since a gain of 1500 on 
oct 22 1987 three days after the stock markets black monday 
crash 
in corporate trading industrials rose moodys investment grade 
corporate bond index which measures total return on a portfolio of 
80 corporate bonds with maturities of five years or longer rose 
429 to 30941 
in the taxexempt market the bond buyer index of 40 actively 
traded municipal bonds rose point to 922732 the average yield 
to maturity dropped to 752 percent from 760 percent 
yields on threemonth treasury bills tumbled to 847 percent as 
the discount fell 24 basis points to 819 percent yields on 
sixmonth bills fell to 865 percent as the discount dropped 23 
basis points to 819 percent yields on 1year bills fell to 873 
percent as the discount fell 26 basis points to 809 percent 
a basis point is onehundredth of a percentage point the yield 
is the annualized return on an investment in a treasury bill the 
discount is the percentage that bills are selling below the face 
value which is paid at maturity 
the federal funds rate the interest on overnight loans between 
banks traded at 9916 percent down from 91116 late thursday 
