<TEXT>
rose blumkin the 95yearold russian 
immigrant who founded the nebraska furniture mart said friday she 
has quit the business in a dispute with her grandsons over control 
of the store 
i got mad and quit said mrs blumkin who began selling 
furniture out of a basement in 1937 and later became known to the 
community as mrs b 
the furniture mart is the nations largest furniture store at a 
single location with 300000 square feet of retail space 
warren buffetts berkshire hathaway inc bought 90 percent of 
the store in 1983 for 55 million but mrs blumkin retained the 
title of board chairwoman and remained a fixture on the sales 
floor selling carpeting and furniture from atop her motorized golf 
cart 
she said she has been angry for some time at her grandsons 
ronald blumkin 40 president and chief executive officer of the 
furniture mart and irvin blumkin 37 vice president 
they are sons of louie blumkin 69 who ran the furniture mart 
along with his mother for years and who still has a major role at 
the store 
mrs blumkin said she is not upset with her son but told the 
omaha worldherald she has used the name hitler to refer to 
grandsons ronald and irvin the blumkins are jewish 
nobody wanted her to leave louie blumkin said friday she 
left on her own 
its such a marvelous family and such a generational gap 
buffett said in an interview from washington dc 
what she did i know im not capable of doing shes one of a 
kind shes one of my heroes he said 
because of the way the deal was structured louie blumkins 
family has increased its ownership to 20 percent with berkshire 
hathaway retaining 80 percent 
mrs blumkin said that in the past she had been respected by her 
family and the stores employees as well as by customers and 
suppliers she fled russia at the age of 23 and began selling 
furniture in the basement of her husbands secondhand clothing 
store in 1937 
mrs blumkin said her work has been her life putting in 6 days 
per week 60 to 70 hours a week 
its awfully lonely not to do nothing i need work i go 
nuts she told the newspaper 
the furniture marts sales of furniture carpets and appliances 
reached 1525 million last year 
